%description:
Remaining TCP_INFO fields (extends TcpStatusInfo beyond what
topic/packetdrill-tcp-info-bridge already landed): caState, backoff, lost,
probes, bytesReceived, deliveredCePkts, deliveredCeBytes.

Client sends a 5-segment (5000B, mss=1000) burst; the tester drops every one
of the server's ACKs for it, so nothing is ever acknowledged and the REXMIT
timer (initialRto=3s) fires at t=4s. RFC 5681 slow start after RTO retransmits
only ONE segment (TcpReno::processRexmitTimer -> retransmitOneSegment), so
snd_nxt (snd_una+1000) stays below snd_max (snd_una+5000) -- afterRto stays
observably true until a later event catches snd_nxt up, unlike a single-
segment-outstanding RTO where the retransmission's own sendSegment() call
clears afterRto again before any external STATUS query could ever observe it
(this was tried first, empirically, against tcp_persist_1.test's zero-window
scenario, and always read back caState=Open -- not what's pinned below).

Falsification: none needed as a separate run -- the two %contains blocks pin
genuinely different caState/backoff values at the two query times, so a stub
returning a fixed sentinel regardless of connection state would fail one of
them.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

sim-time-limit = 10s

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false

# Drop every server ACK from the second one on (b001 is the SYN-ACK, kept so
# the handshake completes normally); a generous range covers however many
# per-segment ACKs the server actually emits for the 5-segment burst.
*.tcptester.script="b2 delete;b3 delete;b4 delete;b5 delete;b6 delete;b7 delete;b8 delete"

*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=5000B
*.cli_app.sendScript=""
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
# t=0.5: idle baseline (Open, no probes/backoff yet). t=4.2: shortly after the
# t=4s RTO fires and retransmits one segment, afterRto still true (see above).
*.cli_app.statusRequestScript="0.5,4.2"

*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.sendScript=""
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s

# tcp settings -- initialWindow must be overridden to "rfc6928" (IW10) so all
# 5 segments of the burst go out immediately instead of ramping up from 1 MSS;
# per the ini first-match-wins gotcha this override must precede the include.
*.*_tcp.initialWindow = "rfc6928"
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.advertisedWindow = 20000

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
STATUS: caState=0 backoff=0 lost=4294967295 probes=0 bytesReceived=0 deliveredCePkts=0 deliveredCeBytes=0
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
STATUS: caState=4 backoff=1 lost=4294967295 probes=0 bytesReceived=0 deliveredCePkts=0 deliveredCeBytes=0
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
